  # Add images

  Let's say you want to add logo.jpg on your index page.
  Add logo.gif to

      public/images

  **Important**: Using `<img src="/images/logo.jpg" />` will work when using the Wagon webserver, but it won't in LocomotiveCMS after deploying to your site.
  Liquid filters are used to get public urls (images, javascripts, stylesheets...).

  In your page, add:

      {% raw %}<img src="{{ 'logo.jpg' | theme_image_url }}" alt="" />{% endraw %}

  Note that your image path is simplier, you don't need to specify the "image" folder. Still, you can create subfolders:

      public/images/icons/ajax-loader.gif

  will be refered this way:

      {% raw %}<img src="{{ 'icons/ajax-loader.gif' | theme_image_url }}" alt="" />{% endraw %}

  <div class="alert alert-info">
  <strong>Note:</strong> In your stylesheets,  images paths in the url() function will be automatically changed to the theme image url.
  </div>

  The [theme\_image\_tag](/references/filters/html/theme_image_tag) can also be used to generate the html img tag:

      {% raw %}{{ 'icons/ajax-loader.gif' | theme_image_tag }}{% endraw %}

  # Add javascripts

  Put your javascripts in the `public/javascripts` folder then use the javascript_tag:

      {% raw %}{{ 'libs/jquery-1.8.2.min' | javascript_tag }}{% endraw %}

  **Note:** You can also use the javascript\_url tag.

  # Add stylesheets

  Put your javascripts in the `public/stylesheets` folder then use the [stylesheet_tag](templates/filters/html/stylesheet_tag):

      {% raw %}{{ 'styles.css' | stylesheet_tag: 'screen, projection' }}{% endraw %}

  **Note:** You can also use the stylesheet\_url tag.


